'''Oren Ben-Dor''' ({{lang-he|אורן בן דור
}}) is a former professor of law and philosophy<ref name="independent">Oren Ben-Dor, [https://www.independent.co.uk/opinion/commentators/oren-bendor-who-are-the-real-terrorists-in-the-middle-east-409291.html Oren Ben-Dor: "Who are the real terrorists in the Middle East?"], ''[[CounterPunch]]'', July 26, 2006.</ref> at the [[University of Southampton]] School of Law in the [[United Kingdom]]. He has published two books on these topics and edited a third on the troubled relationship between law and art. He has been published in various academic and mainstream publications.

He received his Bachelor of Laws from [[Birmingham University]] (1992), and his Master of Arts (1993) and Doctor of Philosophy (1997) from [[University College London]].<ref name=AcademicBio>[http://www.southampton.ac.uk/law/staff/academicstaff/ben-dor_oren.html University of Southampton Law School Academic Biography of Oren Ben-Dor].</ref>

Ben-Dor was born in [[Nahariya]], northern Israel. He has supported academic boycotts of Israel universities,<ref>Oren Ben-Dor, [https://www.independent.co.uk/opinion/commentators/oren-bendor-the-boycott-should-continue-492539.html The boycott should continue: A fight to foster real academic freedom in Israel should unite academics all over the world], ''[[The Independent]]'', May 30, 2005.</ref><ref>Oren Ben-Dor, [http://www.counterpunch.org/bendor05212005.html Academic Freedom in Israel is Central to Resolving the Conflict; To Create It, an Academic Boycott is Needed], ''[[CounterPunch]]'', Weekend Edition, May 21 / 22, 2005.</ref> writing that those on the Israeli "left" who oppose it are "sophisticated accomplices to the smothering of debate."<ref>[http://weekly.ahram.org.eg/2005/747/op13.htm Academic freedom in context], ''[[Al-Ahram Weekly]]'', Issue No. 747, June 16–22, 2005.</ref> He has written about alleged [[Israel and the apartheid analogy|apartheid]] in Israel,<ref>Oren Ben-Dor, [http://www.counterpunch.org/bendor06232007.html Israeli Apartheid is the Core of the Crisis], ''[[CounterPunch]]'', 24 June 2007.</ref> bias in Israel's education system,<ref>[http://goliath.ecnext.com/coms2/gi_0199-6514515/The-portrayal-of-Arabs-in.html The portrayal of Arabs in textbooks in the Jewish school system in Israel], ''[[Arab Studies Quarterly]]'', January 1, 2007.</ref> the ethical and legal challenges facing Palestine,<ref>Oren Ben-Dor, [http://counterpunch.org/bendor12152005.html Ethical and Legal Challenges Facing Palestine], ''[[CounterPunch]]'', December 15, 2005.</ref> and the use of violence by the Israeli state.<ref>Tom McGurk, [http://www.sbpost.ie/post/pages/p/story.aspx-qqqt=TOM+MCGURK-qqqs=commentandanalysis-qqqid=38583-qqqx=1.asp Gaza is at the centre of an unwinnable war], ''[[The Sunday Business Post]]'', January 4, 2009.</ref>

As a contributor to the newsletter ''[[CounterPunch]]'', he has written against Israel's role in the [[2006 Lebanon War]]<ref name="independent"/> and in the [[Gaza War (2008–09)|Gaza War]] of December 2008 to January 2009. Criticizing Israel's tactics against [[Hamas]], Ben-Dor wrote that "assassinating individual members of Hamas, even toppling the organisation, destroying its infrastructure and buildings, will not destroy the legitimate opposition to the arrogant and self-righteous Zionist entity."<ref>Oren Ben-Dor, "[http://www.counterpunch.org/2009/01/01/the-self-defense-of-suicide/ The Self-Defense of Suicide]", ''[[CounterPunch]]'', January 1, 2009.</ref> In 2007, he joined a number of intellectuals and activists in signing a "One State Declaration" which calls for [[One-state solution|one democratic state]] in the whole of Israel and Palestine.<ref>[http://weekly.ahram.org.eg/2007/876/op9.htm Just one state], ''[[Al-Ahram Weekly]]'', Issue No. 876, December 20–26, 2007.</ref> He has supported that alternative in public debate.<ref>Arvind Sivaramakrishnan, [http://www.hindu.com/2008/07/24/stories/2008072452811000.htm A one-state solution for Israel and Palestine], ''[[The Hindu]]'', July 24, 2008.</ref> Ben-Dor has engaged in academic debate with [[Oren Yiftachel]] in the journal ''[[Holy Land Studies]]'' regarding the one-state solution.<ref>Yiftachel, Oren, (2007), "II. From Ethnocracy to Peace through Gradual Bi-Nationalism: A Response to Oren Ben-Dor", ''[[Holy Land Studies]]: A Multidisciplinary Journal'', Volume 6, Number 2, November 187-195</ref><ref>Ben-Dor, Oren (2007) "Debating Israeli Ethnocracy and the Challenge of Secular Democracy: I. A Critique of Oren Yiftachel", ''[[Holy Land Studies]]: A Multidisciplinary Journal'', Volume 6, Number 2, November</ref>

